  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The commonly used Arabic-BERT pre-trained models include mini-BERT, medium-BERT, base-BERT, and large-BERT (Devlin et al. 2018).",
    "The mini-BERT model was designed in order to have a smaller memory consumption and a smaller size than the original BERT model (Almaliki et al. 2023).",
    "This can be achieved by reducing either the number of layers or the hidden size of the transformer model.",
    "In addition to being more computationally efficient, mini-BERT requires fewer computational resources during training and inference due to its downsized architecture.",
    "Even though it may not perform as well as larger BERT models, it can still capture contextual information and semantic relationships within a text in Arabic."
  ],
